// Searxly — committed base build configuration.
//
// SEARXLY_GATEWAY_APP_TOKEN is the *app token* that lets Searxly reach the Searxly gateway
// (keyless token swaps via 0x, plus history). It is a soft gate, NOT the upstream 0x / io.net
// secret — those keys live only on the gateway server (see gateway/gateway.mjs) and never ship
// inside the app. The token is intentionally blank in the public source; the real value is
// layered in from the gitignored Secrets.xcconfig (copy Secrets.example.xcconfig → Secrets.xcconfig
// and paste the token). When blank, the wallet falls back to its "bring your own 0x key" path.
SEARXLY_GATEWAY_APP_TOKEN =

// Optional include: present only on a maintainer's machine (gitignored). The `?` means a clean
// checkout / CI / the open-source repo build fine without it.
#include? "Secrets.xcconfig"
